      "csl:pageColumn": "1-0006",
      "rdf:value": "<L>47<pc>1-0006<k1>aMh<k2>aMh<h>1\n1. {#aMh#}¦, {#a/Mhate, AnaMhe, aMhitA, aMhizyate, AMhizwa#} . {%Gehen.%} {#AMhizwa#}\n<ls>BHAṬṬ. 3,25.</ls> <ls n=\"BHAṬṬ.\">15,28.</ls> {#aMhitAsmahe#}\n<ls n=\"BHAṬṬ.\">22,17.</ls> {#AnaMhe cAntikaM pituH#}\n<ls n=\"BHAṬṬ.\">14,51.</ls> {#AnaMhire 'driM prati#}\n<ls n=\"BHAṬṬ.\">3,46.</ls> {#AMhizAtAmASramam#}\n<ls n=\"BHAṬṬ.\">4,4.</ls> {#AMhizata saMgrAmam#}\n<ls n=\"BHAṬṬ.\">15,74.</ls> — <ab>Caus.</ab> {#aMha/yati#} {%schicken%}: {#tamAYjihanmETilayajYaBUmim#}\n<ls n=\"BHAṬṬ.\">2,40.</ls> <ls n=\"BHAṬṬ.\">15,75.</ls> — <ab>Desid.</ab> {#aYjihizate#} {%gehen wollen%}: {#prAcyamAYjihizAMcakre#}\n<ls n=\"BHAṬṬ.\">14,15.</ls>\n<div n=\"v\">— <ab>Vgl.</ab> {#aMhri#} und {#aNGri#}, für die die Wurzel von den Grammatikern vielleicht erst geschaffen worden ist.\n<LEND>"
    },
